e's how you can implement these steps using DevExpress.Spreadsheet:

csharp
코드 복사
using DevExpress.Spreadsheet;
using System.Drawing;

// Assume `excel1` and `excel2` are your SpreadsheetControl instances
Worksheet sheet1 = excel1.Document.Worksheets[0];
Worksheet sheet2 = excel2.Document.Worksheets[0];

// 1. Set Print Area to A4 Size (210mm x 297mm)
sheet1.ActiveView.Orientation = PageOrientation.Portrait;
sheet1.ActiveView.PaperKind = DevExpress.Drawing.Printing.DXPaperKind.A4;

// Optional: Adjust other print settings like margins if needed
sheet1.ActiveView.Margins.Left = 0.5f;
sheet1.ActiveView.Margins.Right = 0.5f;
sheet1.ActiveView.Margins.Top = 0.5f;
sheet1.ActiveView.Margins.Bottom = 0.5f;

// Optional: Scale content to fit the page width
sheet1.ActiveView.FitToPage = true;
sheet1.ActiveView.FitToWidth = 1;

// 2. Insert a New Row at the Top of the Current Sheet
sheet1.Rows.Insert(0);

// 3. Copy UsedRange from `sheet2` to the Top of `sheet1`
Range usedRange2 = sheet2.GetUsedRange();
int usedRows2 = usedRange2.RowCount;
int usedCols2 = usedRange2.ColumnCount;

// Define the target range in `sheet1`
Range targetRange1 = sheet1.Range.FromLTRB(0, 0, usedCols2 - 1, usedRows2 - 1);

// Copy the content including charts
usedRange2.CopyFrom(usedRange2);
sheet1.Cells.CopyFrom(usedRange2, targetRange1, PasteSpecial.All);

// Optional: Apply a style or format to the inserted range
CellStyle insertedHeaderStyle = sheet1.Workbook.Styles.Add("InsertedHeaderStyle");
insertedHeaderStyle.Fill.BackgroundColor = Color.LightGray;
insertedHeaderStyle.Font.Bold = true;
insertedHeaderStyle.Alignment.Horizontal = SpreadsheetHorizontalAlignment.Center;
sheet1.Rows[0].Style = insertedHeaderStyle;

// Auto-fit the columns to content
sheet1.Columns.AutoFit(0, usedCols2 - 1);
Explanation
Set Print Area:
Configure the active view to use the A4 paper size (PageOrientation.Portrait, DXPaperKind.A4).
Adjust margins and fit to page settings as needed.
Insert a New Row:
Use sheet1.Rows.Insert(0) to insert a new row at the top.
Copy UsedRange:
Get the UsedRange from sheet2 and copy it to the newly inserted top row in sheet1.
Apply Optional Styles:
Apply a style to the newly inserted header row if required.
